  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to IDEG for the Referendum on Multiparty Local Governance in Ghana, 2019, engagement</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To engage the dominant political parties with the aim of forging bipartisan consensus on the best approach to amending Articles 55(3) in the December 10, 2019 national referendum and 243 (1) in Parliament. 
To canvass broad-based elite participation and support for the outreach and public education programs on the December 10 national referendum. 
To mobilize massive electoral support for the amendment of Article 55(3) in the forthcoming national referendum such that the stipulated threshold for the approval will be significantly exceeded. 
To secure and manage the resources, i.e. human, funding, technical and operational, vital to strengthening the autonomy and capacity of the IDEG and allied civil society coalition to pursue the project goals and objective</narrative>
  </description>
